Name: Anonymous
ucPa: It cannot be less than 3 years old. They should take all the facts about the car into consideration and look into CarFacts. The car cannot have any dents/ scratches and cannot have been in any accidents. The car should be priced the same as the other cars on Car Facts depending on it's make and model. It must be a manual car. The car cannot have any maintenance issues because it should be fairly new. The car must be either black, white or grey. It cannot have any damage on the interior. I prefer the interior to be leather, otherwise the owner will have to knock down the price for me. The car must have a certain amount of miles depending on what year it is, too much or too little does have an impact on the car and its price. The owner should have been keeping up with service and repairs and must have adequate proof of this. The car cannot be a gas guzzler so no Lincoln's, Jeeps, etc.
whatConf: The question are not asked clearly & the choices are not all applicable
comments: This study seems pointless, Rutgers should not spend money on pointless research. I should be studying for a class instead of taking this time consuming pointless survey. I am paying for an education, not be be part of a study. This study should be done outside of class & researchers should be paying students for the optional participation.
